NODE.JS & EXPRESS
# ─────────────────────────────────────────

- All async route handlers must be wrapped in try/catch or use
  an asyncHandler wrapper — never let unhandled promise rejections
  reach the process.
- Validate all incoming request bodies with zod before touching them.
- Return consistent error shapes:
    { success: false, error: { code: string, message: string } }
- Return consistent success shapes:
    { success: true, data: T }
- Use HTTP status codes correctly:
    200 GET success · 201 POST created · 204 DELETE/no body
    400 validation · 401 unauthenticated · 403 forbidden
    404 not found · 409 conflict · 422 unprocessable · 500 server
- Middleware order: cors → helmet → rateLimit → bodyParser →
  auth → routes → errorHandler
- Never log sensitive fields (passwords, tokens, PII).
  Use a structured logger (pino / winston) — never console.log
  in production code.
